news.title: Gurugram: Road is not ready after four years, residents protest
news.para: The protesters pointed out that in 2018, the GMDA allotted a tender for building a 3.3km-long master road, along with drains, for Rs 18.21 crore.

news.title: Jhabua overshoots revenue target through property registration by 100%
news.para: Based on a rise in the real-estate sector of Jhabua after the tribal-dominated district generated revenue of Rs 19.69 Crore in 2019-20 and Rs 26.94 Crore through registration of properties, the state government had set a target of Rs 24 Crore in 2021-22.

news.title: South Delhi civic body's property tax mop-up at an all-time high of Rs 1,075 crore
news.para: SDMC commissioner Gyanesh Bharti credited the success to the efforts of officials concerned who extended all possible help to the taxpayers and made them understand the need of making the payment before the deadline.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram civic body collects property tax of Rs 88 crore in FY22
news.para: While it fell short of the target of Rs 100 crore, the corporation recorded around 17% increase in property tax collection when compared to the previous year.

news.title: Date for filing property tax extended in urban bodies of Chhattisgarh
news.para: Citizens will now be able to pay property tax in urban bodies till April 15. According to the order issued, the last date for payment of property tax and filing returns in urban bodies was fixed till March 31.

news.title: Chennai civic body hopes to mop up Rs 1,100 crore from revision of property tax
news.para: From 11 lakh houses in the city including core and added areas, the corporation’s property tax target used to be around `850 crore a year, of which it collected around `670 crore.

news.title: Sector names in Greater Noida likely to get replaced by numeric figures
news.para: There has been a demand from a section of residents for renaming the sectors and the local Greater Noida Industrial Development Authority (GNIDA) has formed a committee to take the decision, the officials said.

news.title: Bombay HC dismisses Omkar Realtors' appeal in Worli flat case
news.para: The builder challenged a March 21 order of Justice Girish Kulkarni which had directed the builder to remove, within a week, debris, huge iron struts in the private lift shaft from the flat and install the lift within three months, failing which a court receiver would execute the work.

news.title: Properties on Nagpur's outskirts see huge price appreciation in RR rates
news.para: Ready reckoner rates are a benchmark for paying stamp duty or property tax. Even if a certain property is sold at a lesser price, the duty has to be paid according to the ready reckoner which is the basic minimum rate.

news.title: Construction has resumed at 95% of China Evergrande projects, unit says
news.para: Evergrande has resumed work at 734 developments in all of China as of March 27, including 424 projects recovering to normal construction levels, according to a post on Saturday on the official WeChat of the developer's Pearl River Delta business unit.

news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body mops up Rs 324 crore in property tax
news.para: The collectible demand for the 2021-22 financial year was 340 crore. On the other hand, the GVMC ended the financial year with 186 crore water tax collection – the highest in the last three years.

news.title: Pune civic body collects Rs 1,836 crore while PCMC earns Rs 633 crore from property tax
news.para: Till March 31, the PMC had collected Rs1,836 crore, while the PCMC had collected property tax of Rs633 crore. Last year, owing to the pandemic, the PMC was able to collect Rs1,664 crore, while the PCMC collected Rs557 crore as property tax.

news.title: Nashik civic body earns Rs 149.37 crore through property tax
news.para: An official said the Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) earned Rs 149.37 crore through property tax in the just-concluded financial year, which was the highest property tax collection for the civic body so far in a fiscal.

news.title: Mysuru development body intent on using land lying vacant in layouts
news.para: ​The layouts identified for the new initiative were developed by the erstwhile City Improvement Trust Board (CITB), and subsequently Muda itself. The land in question had originally been acquired to be developed as sites.

news.title: Property tax collection plunges 4% in a year in Coimbatore
news.para: In the 2020-21 financial year, the city corporation had collected 91% of the target amount. In comparison, it could collect just 87.2% of the target amount in the 2021-22 fiscal.
